-- Chesnara profit soars as Swedish life insurance clocks growth
-- By Esha Vaish and Richa Naidu in Bangalore
-- Fri Mar 28, 2014 03:33AM EDT
-- None



March 28 (Reuters) - Insurance-focused takeover specialist Chesnara Plc's <CSN.L> full-year pretax profit more than tripled as Movestic - its Swedish open life insurance business - captured market share.

Chesnara, which mainly buys life insurance funds closed to new customers, said IFRS pretax profit rose to 60.6 million pounds ($100.7 million) in the year ended Dec. 31 from 19.7 million pounds a year earlier. Movestic like-for-like new business volume rose 61.9 percent, Chesnara said. [ID:nRSb3902Da]